      "id": "r1",
      "order": 0,
      "text": "It was more than a century after Harvey had discovered the circulation of the blood that two other scientists, one English and the other French, discovered oxygen. These men saw that when a flame burns it takes something out of the air. That is why a candle goes out when it has been burning for a little time in a small amount of air. It has taken all the oxygen out of the air. You may see this by putting a lighted candle under a cover, so:",
